rlTunnel.name: rlTunnel
rlTunnel.description: The private MIB module definition for Tunneling.

rlTunnelIsatapRobustness.name: rlTunnelIsatapRobustness
rlTunnelIsatapRobustness.description: specifies how many DNS Querys and Router Solicitations should be sent to get the corresponding reply.

rlTunnelIsatapQueryInterval.name: rlTunnelIsatapQueryInterval
rlTunnelIsatapQueryInterval.description: specifies the time interval between sending of DNS Queries before receiving the first reply from the DNS Server.

rlTunnelIsatapRSInterval.name: rlTunnelIsatapRSInterval
rlTunnelIsatapRSInterval.description: specifies the time interval between sending of Router Solicitations before receiving the first reply from the ISATAP Router.

rlTunnelIsatapMinQueryInterval.name: rlTunnelIsatapMinQueryInterval
rlTunnelIsatapMinQueryInterval.description: specifies the minimum time interval between between successive queries of same advertising ISATAP interface.

rlTunnelIsatapMinRSInterval.name: rlTunnelIsatapMinRSInterval
rlTunnelIsatapMinRSInterval.description: specifies the minimum time between successive solicitations of the same advertising ISATAP interface.

rlTunnelIsatapRouterAddress.name: rlTunnelIsatapRouterAddress
rlTunnelIsatapRouterAddress.description: specifies the IPv4 address of ISATAP Router.

rlTunnelIsatapLocalIPv4Address.name: rlTunnelIsatapLocalIPv4Address
rlTunnelIsatapLocalIPv4Address.description: specifies the IPv4 address currently used as IPv4 source address for ISATAP Tunnel.

rlTunnelIfTable.name: rlTunnelIfTable
rlTunnelIfTable.description: This table is parallel to tunnelIfTable, and is used to add/delete tunnel entries to/from that table. In addition it contains private objects.

rlTunnelIfEntry.name: rlTunnelIfEntry
rlTunnelIfEntry.description: Additional configuration parameters for a tunnel interface.

rlTunnelIfEncapsMethod.name: rlTunnelIfEncapsMethod
rlTunnelIfEncapsMethod.description: The encapsulation method used by the tunnel. This field added since it is read-only in standard MIB.

rlTunnelIfLocalAddressSource.name: rlTunnelIfLocalAddressSource
rlTunnelIfLocalAddressSource.description: Defines the method of obtaining Local address for the tunnel interface. Configured - configured by user. Automatic - minimum IP address of the device. Interface - minimum IP address on user specified interface.

rlTunnelIfLocalAddressInterfaceId.name: rlTunnelIfLocalAddressInterfaceId
rlTunnelIfLocalAddressInterfaceId.description: Interface ID, used to determine Local address for tunnel interface if rlTunnelIfLocalAddressSource set to interface.

rlTunnelIfLocalIPv4Address.name: rlTunnelIfLocalIPv4Address
rlTunnelIfLocalIPv4Address.description: Specifies the IPv4 address currently used as IPv4 Local address for IPv6 over IPv4 Tunnel.

rlTunnelIfStatus.name: rlTunnelIfStatus
rlTunnelIfStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

rlTunnelIsatapConfEntry.name: rlTunnelIsatapConfEntry
rlTunnelIsatapConfEntry.description: Additional configuration parameters for a tunnel interface.

rlTunnelIsatapConfRowStatus.name: rlTunnelIsatapConfRowStatus
rlTunnelIsatapConfRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

rlTunnelIsatapPrlEntry.name: rlTunnelIsatapPrlEntry
rlTunnelIsatapPrlEntry.description: Additional configuration parameters for a tunnel interface.

rlTunnelIsatapPrlIfIndex.name: rlTunnelIsatapPrlIfIndex
rlTunnelIsatapPrlIfIndex.description: The index of the interface to which this PRL entry belongs.

rlTunnelIsatapPrlPriority.name: rlTunnelIsatapPrlPriority
rlTunnelIsatapPrlPriority.description: The priority of the entry. Lower value - higher priority.

rlTunnelIsatapPrlAddress.name: rlTunnelIsatapPrlAddress
rlTunnelIsatapPrlAddress.description: IPv4 address of the potential router.

rlTunnelIsatapPrlIsActive.name: rlTunnelIsatapPrlIsActive
rlTunnelIsatapPrlIsActive.description: Whether the PRL entry is active (meaning it has an up to date RA).

rlTunnelIsatapConfRSInterval.name: rlTunnelIsatapConfRSInterval
rlTunnelIsatapConfRSInterval.description: Specifies the time interval between Router Solicitations prior to receiving the first reply from the ISATAP router.

rlTunnelIsatapConfRobustness.name: rlTunnelIsatapConfRobustness
rlTunnelIsatapConfRobustness.description: After a Router Advertisement was received, Router Solicitation messages are sent every Lifetime / (1 + Robustness) seconds, where Lifetime is the Lifetime advertised in the RA.

rlTunnelIPv6EndConfig.name: rlTunnelIPv6EndConfig
rlTunnelIPv6EndConfig.description: Used to indicate end of snmp configuration for IPv6. Can be removed, if mechanism for indicating end config per mib is added to SNMP.
